## Optional: per-developer local config overrides (network-reachable dev)

`appsettings.Development.json`{{#if ui_angular}} and `angular/src/environments/environment.ts`{{/if}}
ship `localhost`-only URLs by default. When running from a remote dev
box / LXC / container where the host{{#if ui_angular}} and SPA{{/if}} must be reachable from
another machine (different IP / hostname), use the **gitignored**
override files that mirror the committed templates:

```bash
# Host side: ASP.NET config override (CORS, RedirectAllowedUrls, AuthServer:Authority, App:SelfUrl, App:AngularUrl)
cp src/${PROJECT_NAME}.HttpApi.Host/appsettings.Development.local.json.template \
   src/${PROJECT_NAME}.HttpApi.Host/appsettings.Development.local.json
# edit REPLACE_ME_HOST → your dev box's IP or hostname
```

{{#if ui_angular}}
```bash
# Angular side: SPA-bundle environment override (apis.default.url, oAuthConfig.issuer, baseUrl, redirectUri)
cp angular/src/environments/environment.local.ts.template \
   angular/src/environments/environment.local.ts
# edit REPLACE_ME_HOST → same value as above
```
{{/if}}

Then:

```bash
# Run host (default URL is launchSettings — override here to bind 0.0.0.0)
dotnet run --project src/${PROJECT_NAME}.HttpApi.Host --urls "https://0.0.0.0:44326"
```

{{#if ui_angular}}
```bash
# Run Angular with the local override + bind 0.0.0.0
yarn --cwd angular start:local
```

`yarn start:local` is a wired script that calls `ng serve --configuration
local --host 0.0.0.0`. The `local` Angular configuration is defined in
`angular.json` and swaps `environment.ts` → `environment.local.ts` via
`fileReplacements`.
{{/if}}

After changing the override URLs, re-run the DbMigrator so the
OpenIDDict seeded client picks up the new `RedirectAllowedUrls` (the
client's per-row allow-list is stored in the database; ABP refreshes
it on each migrator run from `App:RedirectAllowedUrls`):

```bash
dotnet run --project src/${PROJECT_NAME}.DbMigrator
```

**NEVER put secrets in these `*.local.*` files.** Secrets still live
in `appsettings.secrets.json`, loaded by `.AddAppSettingsSecretsJson()`.
The `.local` files are for non-secret URL / IP overrides only.

## Required: PR auto-close keyword — repeat per issue, no comma chains

`Closes #9, #10, #11` auto-closes ONLY `#9`. Repeat the keyword for each issue:

```
Closes #22, closes #23, closes #24
```

or one per line. Verify with `gh pr view <num> --json closingIssuesReferences`
immediately after creation.

