## Dependabot policy

`.github/workflows/dependabot-auto-merge.yml` auto-merges Dependabot PRs
**after `CICD` succeeds** when ALL of these are true:

- The PR title is parseable as `from X.Y.Z to A.B.C` (single-dep PR; grouped
  PRs are skipped because they lack version info in the title)
- `update-type` is `semver-patch` or `semver-minor` (no major-version bumps)
- `package-ecosystem` is NOT `github-actions` (those carry implicit-API risk
  and stay manual)
- The PR has no `do-not-merge` label

Everything else stays open for human review:

- Major version bumps (any ecosystem)
- All github-actions bumps (`docker/*`, `dorny/*`, `actions/*`)
- Grouped Dependabot PRs (title pattern `bump the <name> group`)
- PRs with unparseable titles (defensive fallback if Dependabot's title
  format ever drifts)

**Known limitation — `maintainer-changes` is not enforced.** Dependabot can
flag PRs where the upstream maintainer changed via the `maintainer-changes`
metadata, but that signal is only available through `dependabot/fetch-metadata`,
which does not work in `workflow_run` event contexts. This workflow relies on
title/branch parsing only, so it cannot gate on `maintainer-changes`. The
github-actions exclusion + major-bump skip cover the highest-risk cases; the
`do-not-merge` label remains the per-PR operator override for everything else.

**Per-PR override** — add the `do-not-merge` label to block auto-merge on a
specific PR (e.g., when you want to test the update locally first).

**Disable globally** — rename
`.github/workflows/dependabot-auto-merge.yml` →
`.github/workflows/dependabot-auto-merge.yml.disabled` and push. GitHub
ignores files that don't end in `.yml`/`.yaml`, so auto-merge halts
immediately. To re-enable, rename back.

**Backlog clear** — to apply auto-merge to PRs created before the workflow
existed, trigger manually:

```bash
gh workflow run dependabot-auto-merge.yml -f pr_number=<NNN>
```

**Required repo + org settings** (operator action, one-time):

- Settings → Actions → General → "Workflow permissions" → "Allow GitHub
  Actions to create and approve pull requests" — **ON** (required at BOTH
  the org level and the repo level — the org setting overrides repo).
  Without this, `gh pr review --approve` returns HTTP 422 and the merge
  step fails. Verify via:
  `gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/actions/permissions/workflow` →
  `can_approve_pull_request_reviews: true`.

**Optional repo settings:**

- Settings → General → "Automatically delete head branches" — left OFF in
  this repo. The workflow already passes `--delete-branch` to `gh pr
  merge`, so Dependabot branches clean themselves up regardless of this
  setting. Flipping it would also affect manual merges (broader scope than
  the auto-merge workflow needs).

## Conventions

- **Backend code style:** mandatory braces on all control-flow statements (ReSharper-enforced). Root namespace `${PROJECT_NAME}` everywhere. All custom tables use prefix `${PROJECT_NAME}Consts.DbTablePrefix = "App"`, schema `null`.
- **Inherit `${PROJECT_NAME}AppService`** for application services (sets `LocalizationResource = typeof(${PROJECT_NAME}Resource)`).
- **Inherit `FullAuditedAggregateRoot<Guid>`** for new aggregate roots — gives soft-delete, audit columns, and concurrency stamp for free.
{{#if ui_angular}}
- **Angular components are standalone** with `inject()` DI (see your repo's first standalone component for the canonical pattern). Selectors kebab-case with `app` prefix.
- **Prettier 100-col single-quote**, enforced by lint.
{{/if}}
- **Localization JSON** under `src/${PROJECT_NAME}.Domain.Shared/Localization/${PROJECT_NAME}/` — keep your `${DEFAULT_CULTURE}.json` (default) and any other culture files in sync. Cross-resource ABP keys use `'AbpUi::Delete'` (resource::key), NOT `'::AbpUi:Delete'`.
- **CSP defaults to Report-Only.** `App:Csp:Mode` defaults to `report-only` in `appsettings.json`. Operators ramp to enforcement after a 7-14 day soak by setting `App:Csp:Mode=enforce` (and optionally `App:Csp:ReportUri` to receive violation reports). The CSP middleware is at `src/${PROJECT_NAME}.HttpApi.Host/Middleware/ContentSecurityPolicyMiddleware.cs`.{{#if ui_angular}} The SPA-edge headers (CSP + HSTS + X-Frame-Options + X-Content-Type-Options + Referrer-Policy) live in `angular/nginx.conf`.{{/if}} HSTS on the host starts at 30 days (no `includeSubDomains`, no `preload`) — bump to 1 year after soak; never enable preload without explicit operator sign-off (it is irrevocable in practice).
- **OTel custom Meter naming.** Every custom `System.Diagnostics.Metrics.Meter` instantiated in code uses the prefix `${PROJECT_NAME}.<Feature>` (PascalCase, dot-prefixed) — e.g., `new Meter("${PROJECT_NAME}.<Feature>")`. Instrument names use snake_case + unit suffix (e.g., `<feature>_<event>_total`, `<feature>_<event>_duration_ms`). The OTel Prometheus exporter auto-translates the meter dot-prefix to underscore: scrape view is `${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}_<feature>_<event>_total{...}`. NEVER carry PII (filenames, user ids) in metric tags — only finite-cardinality dimensions like `reason`.

